    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-01T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-01T17:00:00-05:00" n="725"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d725">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/9895a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BRC1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bundy</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-01T18:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 1, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>U.S.S. <hi rend="italic">Raleigh</hi> due to arrive at Monrovia on or about May
                    6. Commanding officer has appropriate instructions. Report fully by cable result
                    of conference between commanding officer and Liberian authorities. Department
                    has advised British and French Governments.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
